dependent%20venues%20and%20arts%20groups%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20pop%20stars%20used%20the%20program%20as%20a%20piggy%20bank%20to%20keep%20the%20party%20going%2C%20reporting%20by%20Business%20Insider%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stars'%20spending%20took%20place%20against%20a%20backdrop%20of%20massive%20pandemic-relief%20fraud.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmall-business-duplicate-loans-paycheck-protection-program-ppp-inspector-general-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaycheck%20Protection%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Economic%20Injury%20Disaster%20Loans%20gave%20out%20as%20much%20as%20%24200%20billion%20in%20suspected%20false%20claims%2C%20losses%20that%20combined%20with%20false%20unemployment-benefit%20claims%20amount%20to%20what%20the%20FBI%20has%20called%20the%20largest%20fraud%20in%20history.%20Compared%20with%20those%20better-known%20programs%2C%20the%20Shuttered%20Venue%20Operators%20Grant%20had%20relatively%20strict%20eligibility%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20accounting%20firms%20and%20money%20managers%20soon%20realized%20their%20stadium-filling%20musician%20clients%20might%20be%20eligible%20for%20grant%20money%20via%20their%20loan-out%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20corporate%20entities%20used%20to%20handle%20the%20business%20of%20touring.%20Grants%20awarded%20to%20clients%20of%20one%20high-powered%20entertainment-business-management%20firm%2C%20NKSFB%2C%20totaled%20at%20least%20%24207%20million%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%20NKSFB%20itself%20collected%20more%20than%20%247%20million%20by%20helping%20its%20clients%20obtain%20the%20grants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENKSFB's%20managing%20partner%2C%20Mickey%20Segal%2C%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%20The%20firm's%20lawyer%20Bryan%20Freedman%20said%20NKSFB%20doesn't%20comment%20on%20its%20clients'%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrantees%20received%20up%20to%20%2410%20million%20that%20they%20could%20spend%20on%20certain%20%26quot%3Bordinary%20and%20necessary%26quot%3B%20expenses%20for%20their%20entertainment%20businesses.%20They%20had%20to%20make%20a%20good-faith%20statement%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsba-loans-small-business-lending-rules-change-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESmall%20Business%20Administration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20oversaw%20the%20program%2C%20that%20the%20grant%20was%20necessary%20to%20support%20the%20loan-out%20company's%20%26quot%3Bongoing%20operations%26quot%3B%20and%20show%20that%20the%20company's%20revenue%20had%20fallen%20by%20at%20least%2025%25%20between%20one%20quarter%20of%202019%20and%20the%20same%20quarter%20of%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20SBA%20said%20it%20followed%20the%20law.%20But%20the%20law%20directed%20the%20SBA%20to%20examine%20revenue%2C%20not%20assets.%20Musicians%20with%20huge%20bank%20accounts%20and%20multiple%20mansions%20were%20still%20eligible%20for%20the%20awards%20as%20long%20as%20their%20loan-out%20company's%20revenue%20had%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20pages%20of%20accounting%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20reveal%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20how%20some%20wealthy%20musicians%20%E2%80%94%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnksfb-svog-blowback-rich-musicians-pandemic-relief-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChris%20Brown%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20DJ%20Marshmello%2C%20and%20members%20of%20Alice%20in%20Chains%20%E2%80%94%20spent%20grants%20they%20received%20through%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20documents%20include%20detailed%20records%20explaining%20how%20celebrity%20musicians%20spent%20their%20grants%2C%20as%20well%20as%20correspondence%20between%20their%20accountants%20and%20the%20SBA.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20reveal%20how%20artists%20directed%20millions%20in%20taxpayer%20funds%20not%20toward%20touring%20crew%20members%2C%20but%20instead%20toward%20their%20own%20bank%20accounts%2C%20luxury%20purchases%2C%20and%20entertainment%20expenses%20%E2%80%94%20often%20while%20sitting%20on%20substantial%20wealth%20from%20other%20business%20ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20top%20government-accountability%20expert%20said%20some%20of%20the%20spending%20Business%20Insider%20identified%20was%20questionable%20%E2%80%94%20but%20stopped%20short%20of%20saying%20it%20was%20fraudulent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20a%20minimum%2C%20it%20smells%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20David%20Walker%2C%20a%20former%20comptroller%20general%20of%20the%20United%20States.%20%26quot%3BWhether%20it's%20legal%20or%20not%20is%20up%20to%20a%20lawyer%20or%20ultimately%20to%20a%20court.%20But%20it%20sure%20smells.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SBA%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Bimplemented%20industry-leading%20fraud%20controls.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Gary%20Peters%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20Committee%20on%20Homeland%20Security%20and%20Governmental%20Affairs%2C%20said%20celebrity%20musicians'%20use%20of%20Shuttered%20Venue%20grants%20was%20%26quot%3Ban%20abuse%20of%20federal%20resources.%26quot%3B%20Business%20Insider's%20findings%2C%20he%20added%2C%20demonstrate%20%26quot%3Bthe%20need%20for%20continued%20oversight%20of%20pandemic-relief%20programs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPandemic%20relief%20was%20intended%20to%20help%20businesses%20and%20workers%20in%20need%2C%20the%20senator%20said%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bnot%20super%20wealthy%20celebrities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e7286d0-fa05-4b6e-8443-8678f096b5ff%5C%22%3EAn%20%2480%2C000%20birthday%20party%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELil%20Wayne%20wasn't%20the%20only%20one%20to%20engage%20in%20questionable%20grant%20spending.%20Chris%20Brown%20spent%20his%20grant%20on%20a%20big%20paycheck%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20big%20party.%20Of%20the%20%2410%20million%20grant%20Brown's%20company%20CBE%20Touring%20received%2C%20%245.1%20million%20went%20to%20Brown%20personally.%20He%20also%20billed%20taxpayers%20nearly%20%2480%2C000%20for%20his%2033rd%20birthday%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20blowout%2C%20held%20in%20a%20luxe%20Los%20Angeles%20event%20space%2C%20featured%20a%20%243%2C650%20LED%20dance%20floor%20and%20%26quot%3Batmosphere%20models%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20nude%20women%20in%20body%20paint%20%E2%80%94%20who%20cost%20%242%2C100%2C%20according%20to%20expense%20reports%20and%20a%20blog%20post%20by%20the%20party%20planner.%20The%20bill%20included%20more%20than%20%2429%2C000%20for%20hookahs%2C%20bottle%20service%2C%20%26quot%3Bnitrogen%20ice%20cream%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20damages%20involving%20burn%20holes%20to%20rented%20couches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20grant%20was%20meant%20to%20support%20live%20entertainment%2C%20Brown%20also%20charged%20%2424%2C000%20to%20the%20grant%20for%20the%20cost%20of%20driving%20his%20tour%20bus%20from%20the%20US%20to%20Tulum%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20back%20in%20fall%202020%20during%20a%20monthlong%20stay%20for%20him%20and%20his%20entourage%20in%20the%20resort%20town%2C%20where%20he%20did%20not%20perform.%20He%20spent%20several%20days%20in%20Tulum%20filming%20a%20video%20with%20Jack%20Harlow%20for%20a%20joint%20track%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20clear%20if%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20trip%20was%20for%20business%20or%20pleasure.%20And%20more%20than%20%24179%2C000%20of%20the%20grant%20went%20toward%20a%20celebrity%20basketball%20tournament%20broadcast%20on%20YouTube%2C%20including%20a%20%2420%2C000%20payment%20to%20the%20Indianapolis%20Colts%20tight%20end%20Mo%20Alie-Cox%2C%20who%20played%20on%20Brown's%20basketball%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fjatn0%2F5%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22What%20Chris%20Brown%20spent%20his%20grant%20on%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22423%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%2C%20his%20attorneys%2C%20and%20managers%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%20Representatives%20for%20Harlow%20and%20Alie-Cox%20also%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20also%20paid%20themselves%2C%20taking%20advantage%20of%20an%20SVOG%20spending%20category%20that%20Business%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsba-svog-grant-pandemic-relief-fund-post-malone-chris-brown-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrew%20attention%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%3A%20%26quot%3Bowner%20compensation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SBA's%20guidance%20said%20artists%20could%20use%20grants%20paid%20to%20their%20loan-out%20company%20to%20pay%20themselves%20as%20long%20as%20the%20check%20was%20no%20bigger%20than%20it%20was%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarshmello%2C%20whose%20real%20name%20is%20Christopher%20Comstock%2C%20received%20a%20%249.9%20million%20grant.%20More%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20when%20the%20SBA%20asked%20for%20proof%20of%20where%20it%20went%2C%20his%20business%20manager%20Steven%20Macauley%2C%20of%20NKSFB%2C%20responded%20by%20saying%20all%20the%20money%20went%20into%20Comstock's%20pocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20the%20beneficiary%20received%202019%20Officer%20Draws%2FSalary%20from%20365%20Touring%20International%2C%20Inc.%20in%20excess%20of%20the%20SVOG%20Grant%20Award%2C%20we%20therefore%2C%20expensed%20the%20entire%20Grant%20balance%20to%20Payroll%2C%26quot%3B%20Macauley%20wrote%20in%20an%20April%202023%20letter%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20because%20Comstock%20made%20more%20than%20%249.9%20million%20from%20touring%20in%202019%2C%20he%20was%20able%20to%20award%20himself%20the%20entire%20grant.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20Comstock%20paid%20himself%20more%20than%20any%20other%20musician%20who%20received%20grant%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComstock's%20publicists%20and%20his%20manager%20didn't%20reply%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%2C%20nor%20did%20Macauley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArtists%20often%20paid%20themselves%20far%20more%20than%20they%20paid%20anyone%20else%20involved%20in%20putting%20on%20their%20live%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20Aoki's%20loan-out%20company%2C%20DJ%20Kid%20Millionaire%20Touring%2C%20used%20%242.4%20million%20in%20grant%20money%20on%20payroll%20costs%2C%20of%20which%20%241.9%20million%20was%20officer%20pay.%20Aoki%20is%20the%20company's%20only%20officer.%20Aoki's%20publicists%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20of%20the%20four%20members%20of%20the%20rock%20band%20Shinedown%20split%20at%20least%20%242.5%20million%20of%20their%20%248.3%20million%20grant.%20On%20top%20of%20those%20distributions%2C%20Shinedown's%20four%20members%20paid%20themselves%20more%20than%20%24100%2C000%20each%20out%20of%20the%20roughly%20%241.2%20million%20of%20the%20grant%20that%20was%20allocated%20to%20payroll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20band's%2015%20touring-production%20workers%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20received%20a%20combined%20%24650%2C000%20of%20the%20grant%20money%20%E2%80%94%20less%20than%20a%20single%20member%20of%20the%20band%20got.%20Publicists%20for%20the%20band%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecords%20seen%20by%20BI%20show%20that%20a%20good%20chunk%20of%20the%20%247.7%20million%20grant%20to%20Sremm%20Touring%2C%20the%20loan-out%20company%20for%20the%20hip-hop%20duo%20Rae%20Sremmurd%2C%20was%20paid%20to%20the%20rappers%20Slim%20Jxmmi%20and%20Swae%20Lee%2C%20whose%20real%20names%20are%20Aaquil%20Brown%20and%20Khalif%20Brown.%20The%20duo's%20manager%2C%20lawyer%2C%20and%20publicists%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2023%2C%202022%2C%20records%20show%2C%20the%20Alice%20in%20Chains%20singer%20and%20guitarist%20Jerry%20Cantrell%20took%20in%20%241.4%20million%20as%20an%20%26quot%3BSVOG%20distribution.%26quot%3B%20The%20band's%20drummer%2C%20Sean%20Kinney%2C%20received%20the%20same%20amount%2C%20and%20its%20bassist%2C%20Mike%20Inez%2C%20booked%20half%20that%20sum%2C%20about%20%24682%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20all%2C%20%243.4%20million%20of%20the%20%244.1%20million%20the%20grant%20allotted%20for%20payroll%20went%20to%20the%20three%20musicians%20at%20the%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20grant%20applicants%2C%20AIC%20Entertainment%20%E2%80%94%20the%20three%20band%20members'%20touring%20business%20%E2%80%94%20had%20to%20tell%20the%20government%20only%20that%20the%20money%20was%20%26quot%3Bnecessary.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20month%20before%20they%20took%20their%20grant%20payments%2C%20the%20band%20members%20recorded%20about%20%2448%20million%20in%20income%20from%20selling%20the%20copyrights%20on%20their%20catalog.%20They%20made%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20more%20from%20merchandise%20sales%20and%20other%20profit%20distributions%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20band%20spent%20some%20money%20to%20pay%20its%20staff.%20It%20paid%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20sound-equipment-rental%20firms%2C%20videographers%2C%20and%20managers.%20But%20the%20precarious%20nature%20of%20working%20in%20the%20live-entertainment%20business%20didn't%20change%20for%20some%20of%20its%20employees.%20Scott%20Dachroeden%2C%20a%20guitar%20tech%20and%20tour%20photographer%20who%20had%20worked%20with%20the%20band%20for%20years%2C%20received%20a%20cancer%20diagnosis%20in%20late%202022.%20The%20band%2C%20which%20records%20show%20did%20not%20spend%20grant%20money%20on%20benefits%20like%20health%20insurance%2C%20circulated%20a%20GoFundMe%20page%20on%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20has%20no%20health%20insurance%20and%20now%20cannot%20work%20to%20pay%20his%20bills%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20page%20said.%20The%20band's%20lead%20singer%20said%20on%20Facebook%20that%20Alice%20in%20Chains%20helped%20out%20behind%20the%20scenes%2C%20but%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20situation%20said%20that%20Dachroeden%20didn't%20get%20much%2C%20if%20any%2C%20money%20from%20the%20band%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20that%20after%20his%20diagnosis%2C%20the%20band%20connected%20Dachroeden%20with%20a%20charity%20that%20helps%20with%20medical%20bills.%20Dachroeden%20died%20soon%20after%20his%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlice%20in%20Chain's%20publicists%20and%20manager%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3b11664-2704-4a33-b803-5be2d7156c73%5C%22%3ESupporting%20'middle-class%20people'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Shuttered%20Venue%20Operators%20Grant%20program%20was%20pitched%20to%20Americans%20as%20a%20way%20to%20ensure%20that%20arts%20groups%20would%20still%20exist%20after%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20James%20Corden%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Late%20Late%20Show%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchuck-schumer-career-house-to-senate-majority-leader-new-york-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChuck%20Schumer%3C%2Fa%3E%20cast%20it%20as%20a%20way%20to%20protect%20%26quot%3Bmiddle-class%20people%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Byoung%20artists%26quot%3B%20while%20pandemic%20restrictions%20forced%20closures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrant%20money%20would%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20these%20folks%20going%26quot%3B%20so%20that%20%26quot%3Bthese%20live%20venues%20will%20be%20out%20there%20bigger%20and%20better%20than%20ever%26quot%3B%20after%20the%20restrictions%20lift%2C%20Schumer%20said.%20Schumer's%20press%20office%20and%20chief%20of%20staff%20didn't%20respond%20to%20comment%20requests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chuck%20Schumer%20accepts%20a%20Grammy%20on%20the%20Hill%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67607082279d913c37cbaa30%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%202023%2C%20Sen.%20Chuck%20Schumer%20received%20a%20Grammy%20on%20the%20Hill%20for%20his%20work%20on%20the%20Shuttered%20Venue%20Operators%20Grant.%20%26quot%3BI%20believe%20in%20the%20power%20of%20the%20music%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20the%20awards%20event.%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20always%2C%20always%20fight%2C%20tooth%20and%20nail%2C%20Brooklyn%20style%2C%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EPaul%20Morigi%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20more%20than%2013%2C000%20arts%20groups%20received%20grants%2C%20including%20some%20who%20say%20they%20wouldn't%20still%20exist%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20shutdowns%20happened%2C%20it%20was%20existential.%20Immediate%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Brandy%20Hotchner%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Arizona%20Actors%20Academy%2C%20an%20acting%20school%20in%20Phoenix.%20The%20grant%20of%20less%20than%20%24120%2C000%20the%20group%20received%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Butterly%20saved%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusicians%20weren't%20explicitly%20categorized%20as%20eligible%20%E2%80%94%20and%20initially%2C%20the%20SBA%20interpreted%20the%20law%20to%20mean%20that%20artists'%20loan-out%20companies%20couldn't%20qualify%20for%20the%20grant%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20mid-December%202021%2C%20for%20reasons%20BI%20was%20unable%20to%20determine%2C%20the%20agency%20had%20reversed%20that%20decision%2C%20according%20to%20an%20internal%20memo%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20which%20cleared%20the%20way%20for%20federal%20funding%20to%20flow%20to%20wealthy%20artists.%20The%20SBA%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20question%20about%20why%20it%20reversed%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business-management%20firm%20NKSFB%20also%20made%20millions%20from%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPartners%20at%20the%20firm%20initially%20believed%20that%20their%20celebrity%20clients%20didn't%20qualify%20for%20the%20grants.%20At%20least%20one%20partner%20feared%20that%20applying%20could%20be%20perjury%2C%20and%20another%2C%20Rob%20Salzman%2C%20thought%20the%20whole%20thing%20was%20%26quot%3Bbullshit%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20court%20document%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Billboard%20magazine%20as%20part%20of%20its%20list%20of%20%26quot%3BTop%20Business%20Managers%2C%26quot%3B%20Salzman%20said%20that%20applying%20for%20the%20grants%20was%20an%20example%20of%20the%20firm's%20%26quot%3Boutside-the-box%26quot%3B%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20of%20heart%20led%20to%20a%20big%20payday.%20Court%20documents%20show%20the%20firm%20made%20at%20least%20%247.5%20million%20in%20fees%20on%20the%20grants.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESalzman%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNKSFB%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20respected%20business%20management%20firms%20in%20the%20world%2C%20does%20not%20comment%20on%20its%20clients'%20financial%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Freedman%2C%20the%20firm's%20lawyer.%20%26quot%3BBased%20on%20the%20uninformed%20questions%20that%20BI%20has%20asked%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20it%20has%20little%20to%20no%20understanding%20on%20this%20subject.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20white-collar%20professionals%20also%20outearned%20techs%20and%20roadies.%20Lawyers%20at%20the%20celebrity-favorite%20firms%20Greenberg%20Traurig%20and%20Grubman%20Shire%20Meiselas%20%26amp%3B%20Sacks%20received%20up%20to%205%25%20of%20their%20clients'%20grants.%20Brown's%20manager%20took%207%25%20of%20his%20grant%2C%20and%20Shinedown's%20managers%20received%2020%25%20of%20theirs.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Greenberg%20Traurig%20didn't%20answer%20questions%20about%20the%20firm's%20actions.%20Partners%20at%20Grubman%20Shire%20didn't%20respond%20to%20emails%20or%20phone%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20%242.1%20million%20of%20Lil%20Wayne's%20grant%20paid%20off%20a%20debt%20to%20a%20former%20manager%2C%20Cortez%20Bryant.%20Another%20%24300%2C000%20went%20to%20a%20former%20accountant%2C%20and%20his%20manager%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Mack%20Maine%2C%20whose%20real%20name%20is%20Jermaine%20Preyan%2C%20took%20%241.7%20million.%20All%20told%2C%20roughly%20%245.3%20million%20went%20to%20managers%2C%20accountants%2C%20and%20attorneys%20as%20fees%20and%20commissions%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%2013%20times%20the%20amount%20Lil%20Wayne%20paid%20the%20drummer%2C%20sound%20techs%2C%20and%20other%20contractors%20who%20helped%20put%20on%20his%20live%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBryant%20and%20Preyan%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lil%20Wayne%20performing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6760716527808b3289cd615c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELil%20Wayne%20used%20federal%20funds%20to%20buy%20clothes%20for%20himself%20and%20several%20of%20his%20associates%20to%20wear%20at%20a%20music%20festival%20promoting%20his%20marijuana%20brand%2C%20GKUA.%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20in%20March%20that%20the%20SBA%20didn't%20question%20his%20claim%20that%20he%20ran%20a%20drug-free%20workplace%2C%20even%20though%20he%20often%20smokes%20weed%20onstage.%3Cp%3ERich%20Fury%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20music-industry%20insider%20who%20learned%20from%20Business%20Insider%20about%20NKSFB's%20wave%20of%20grant%20applications%20said%20he%20was%20stunned%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20approved%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20never%20crossed%20my%20mind%20that%20we%20should%20be%20trying%20to%20get%20this%20money%20for%20my%20artists%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20insider%2C%20an%20artist%20manager%20who%20was%20involved%20in%20lobbying%20lawmakers%20to%20pass%20the%20legislation%20and%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20because%20of%20the%20issue's%20sensitivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20in%20countless%20conversations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20ever%20discussed%20artists%20collecting%20this%20money.%20It%20never%20came%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHotchner%2C%20the%20acting-school%20founder%2C%20said%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bspeechless%26quot%3B%20upon%20learning%20about%20Business%20Insider's%20reporting%20on%20how%20celebrity%20musicians%20spent%20their%20grants.%20Though%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20sent%20to%20pop%20stars%20is%20small%20relative%20to%20the%20overall%20amount%20of%20money%20disbursed%20through%20the%20grant%20program%2C%20she%20said%20she%20worried%20it%20would%20taint%20the%20public's%20perception%20of%20government%20support%20for%20the%20arts%20%E2%80%94%20support%20that's%20still%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20never%20forget%20how%20hard-fought-for%20this%20funding%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20such%20a%20disappointment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22019182c7-b77c-4984-9d17-45e5c481d578%5C%22%3E'Shut%20up%2C%20sit%20down.%20Process%20the%20file.'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20Congress%20created%20the%20program%2C%20lawmakers%20began%20pressing%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20to%20get%20money%20out%20the%20door.%20By%20mid-June%202021%2C%20more%20than%20200%20members%20of%20Congress%20had%20signed%20two%20separate%20letters%20demanding%20the%20agency%20disburse%20the%20funds%20expeditiously%2C%20saying%20arts%20organizations%20could%20go%20out%20of%20business%20without%20immediate%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SBA%20said%20congressional%20pressure%20%26quot%3Bwas%20not%20the%20driving%20factor%26quot%3B%20behind%20changes%20that%20sped%20up%20the%20grant%20process%20and%20merely%20%26quot%3Bcoincided%26quot%3B%20with%20changes%20it%20was%20already%20making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20hoped%20to%20balance%20a%20quick%20release%20of%20funds%20with%20a%20desire%20to%20protect%20against%20large-scale%20fraud%20that%20had%20plagued%20other%20pandemic%20programs.%20Its%20compromise%20was%20to%20relax%20some%20anti-fraud%20controls%20on%20the%20front%20end%20of%20the%20grant%20process%2C%20a%20report%20from%20the%20SBA's%20inspector%20general%20said.%20Instead%2C%20it%20planned%20to%20verify%20whether%20the%20grantees%20were%20actually%20eligible%20and%20how%20the%20money%20was%20spent%20after%20distributing%20the%20grants.%20In%20its%20response%20to%20the%20inspector%20general's%20report%2C%20the%20agency%20said%20it%20disagreed%20with%20the%20conclusion%20that%20changes%20to%20how%20it%20evaluated%20applications%20amounted%20to%20%26quot%3Bweakened%26quot%3B%20fraud%20controls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20approach%20had%20mixed%20results.%20The%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20said%20that%20it%20submitted%20three%20phony%20applications%20to%20the%20program%20and%20that%20all%20three%20were%20rejected.%20But%20some%20of%20the%20eight%20current%20and%20former%20SBA%20workers%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20said%20they%20felt%20the%20agency%20was%20too%20permissive%20and%20ignored%20or%20misinterpreted%20relevant%20rules%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20allowing%20grantees%20to%20spend%20federal%20funds%20on%20thousands%20of%20dollars'%20worth%20of%20alcohol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20just%20trying%20to%20get%20money%20out.%20If%20it%20was%20fraudulent%2C%20if%20it%20was%20not%20eligible%20%E2%80%94%20whatever%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20person%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20grants%20said.%20They%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20because%20they%20feared%20retaliation%2C%20but%20their%20identity%20is%20known%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SBA's%20inspector%20general%20criticized%20the%20agency's%20decision%20to%20spot%20problems%20after%20the%20recipients%20already%20spent%20the%20money%2C%20saying%20it%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20provide%20sufficient%20fraud%20prevention%20and%20comes%20at%20a%20point%20when%20funds%20are%20potentially%20unrecoverable.%26quot%3B%20Some%20SBA%20employees%20said%20that%20as%20the%20program%20began%20to%20wind%20down%2C%20they%20were%20pressured%20to%20certify%20recipients'%20compliance%20with%20program%20rules%20rather%20than%20dig%20through%20detailed%20records%20of%20their%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SBA%20said%20in%20September%20it%20had%20recouped%20%2443%20million%20worth%20of%20the%20grants%20%E2%80%94%20an%20amount%20that%20hadn't%20increased%20since%20July.%20It's%20not%20clear%20how%20the%20agency%20recovered%20that%20money.%20While%20the%20SBA%20has%20a%20team%20to%20recover%20wrongfully%20awarded%20grants%2C%20an%20organizational%20chart%20suggests%20that%20as%20of%20late%20September%20it%20hadn't%20assigned%20any%20staff%20to%20it.%20Documents%20obtained%20in%20a%20public-records%20request%20said%20%246%20billion%20worth%20of%20grants%20remain%20under%20review%20for%20compliance%20with%20program%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SBA%20said%20%26quot%3Bsome%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20grants%20Business%20Insider%20mentioned%20in%20its%20reporting%20%26quot%3Bremain%20open%20due%20to%20ongoing%20third-party%20audits%20that%20the%20Agency%20is%20resolving.%26quot%3B%20The%20agency%20spokesperson%20didn't%20respond%20to%20questions%20about%20recoupment%20and%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20follow-up%20question%20asking%20which%20grants%20remain%20unresolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20people%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20program%20said%20they%20tried%20to%20raise%20concerns%20about%20grantees'%20eligibility%20and%20spending%20to%20supervisors%2C%20to%20no%20avail.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20never%20so%20disappointed%20in%20my%20fellow%20man%20than%20in%20that%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20people%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20graft%20was%20unbelievable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20those%20people%20said%20they%20were%20frustrated%20the%20agency%20wasn't%20doing%20more%20to%20investigate%20possible%20misspending%20and%20recover%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20kept%20saying%20shut%20up%2C%20sit%20down.%20Process%20the%20file%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20current%20SBA%20employee%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20because%20they're%20not%20authorized%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20person%20said%20that%20while%20some%20issues%20stemmed%20from%20the%20dwindling%20number%20of%20SVOG%20employees%20drowning%20in%20documentation%2C%20other%20problems%20arose%20because%20of%20the%20way%20the%20program%20was%20administered.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20our%20fault%20because%20we%20threw%20this%20thing%20together%20in%20five%20seconds%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20SBA%20spokesperson%20defended%20its%20processes.%20%26quot%3BBy%20design%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20processing%20staff%20did%20not%20have%20access%20to%20the%20complete%20results%20of%20fraud%20checks%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20are%20not%20positioned%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20internal%20review%20process%20or%20its%20outcomes%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhere%20credible%20evidence%20suggests%20funds%20were%20misspent%20or%20a%20grantee%20misrepresented%20their%20expenditures%20to%20SBA%2C%20the%20agency's%20robust%20fraud%20and%20waste%20oversight%20structure%20reviewed%20such%20allegations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20substantiated%2C%20SBA%20and%20its%20law%20enforcement%20partners%20vigorously%20prosecute%20suspected%20wrongdoing.%20As%20a%20matter%20of%20policy%2C%20the%20SBA%20cannot%20comment%20on%20specific%20investigations%20or%20law%20enforcement%20action%2C%20whether%20planned%20or%20ongoing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20government%20has%20recovered%20at%20least%20some%20money%20from%20one%20musician.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20pandemic%20restrictions%20faded%2C%20Chris%20Brown%20returned%20to%20performing.%20In%20early%202022%2C%20he%20announced%20a%2027-stop%20nationwide%20tour%20and%20launched%20a%20variety%20of%20side%20projects%2C%20including%20a%20novelty%20cereal%20called%20Breezy's%20Cosmic%20Crunch%20and%20an%20NFT%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20was%20disbursing%20money%20to%20Brown's%20touring%20company%2C%20federal%20and%20state%20tax%20authorities%20were%20becoming%20very%20interested%20in%20his%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202021%2C%20the%20IRS%20notified%20Brown%20that%20he%20owed%20%243.2%20million%20in%20unpaid%20taxes.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20IRS%20determined%20that%20Brown%20owed%20an%20additional%20%242.2%20million%2C%20while%20California's%20Franchise%20Tax%20Board%20found%20that%20Brown%20hadn't%20paid%20%241.3%20million%20in%20state%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20settled%20these%20debts%20in%20April%20last%20year%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20before%20American%20taxpayers%20had%20unwittingly%20paid%20%2480%2C000%20for%20his%20birthday%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Know%20more%3F%20Reach%20Jack%20Newsham%20via%20email%20(%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajnewsham%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Ejnewsham%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E)%20or%20via%20Signal%20(%2B1-314-971-1627).%20Do%20not%20use%20a%20work%20device.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flil-wayne-chris-brown-covid-relief-funds-svog-grant-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734516181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67059613a703186492805f96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flil-wayne-chris-brown-covid-relief-funds-svog-grant-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pop%20stars%20took%20advantage%20of%20the%20SVOG%20grant%2C%20using%20COVID%20relief%20funds%20for%20luxury%20spending.%20Li