ception%20101.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ENatalist%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20running%20Natalist%2C%20overseeing%20women's%20health%20strategy%20at%20Everly%20Health%20after%20Natalist%20was%20acquired%2C%20and%20then%20cofounding%20egg%20donation%20startup%20Cofertility%2C%20Tecco%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20second%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20pregnant%20a%20second%20time%20proved%20even%20more%20difficult.%20Tecco%20endured%20multiple%20unsuccessful%20rounds%20of%20IVF%20and%20eleven%20miscarriages%2C%20over%20nearly%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrowing%20herself%20into%20her%20work%20did%20little%20to%20help%20her%20escape%20the%20heartbreak.%20Infertility%20and%20pregnancy%2C%20as%20she%20spent%20her%20spare%20time%20helping%20thousands%20of%20patients%20trying%20to%20conceive%2C%20were%20always%20on%20her%20mind.%20She%20wrestled%20with%20jealousy%20over%20other%20people's%20%26quot%3Bmiracle%20babies%26quot%3B%20as%20she%20waited%20desperately%20for%20her%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecondary%20infertility%2C%20the%20difficulty%20of%20having%20another%20child%20after%20a%20previous%20successful%20pregnancy%2C%20robbed%20Tecco%20of%20countless%20hours%20of%20her%20life%20and%20plenty%20of%20happiness.%20Miscarrying%20twins%20at%2017%20weeks%20pregnant%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20time%20in%20my%20years%20where%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20plan%20B%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.halletecco.com%2Fblog%2Fsecondary-infertility%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%202023%20blog%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20paused%20fertility%20treatments%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202022%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20her%20family.%20After%20much%20reflection%20and%20therapy%2C%20she%20realized%20that%20%26quot%3Bovercoming%26quot%3B%20her%20secondary%20infertility%20wouldn't%20mean%20having%20another%20child.%20It%20meant%20making%20peace%20with%20the%20idea%20that%20she%20never%20would.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20harder%20than%20I%20can%20explain%20to%20make%20that%20decision%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20someone%20like%20me%2C%20where%20you're%20like%2C%20I%20want%20this%20thing%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20get%20this%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Tecco%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20go%20into%20my%2040s%20being%20really%20clear%20about%20my%20intentions%20of%20moving%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cofertility%20cofounders%20Halle%20Tecco%2C%20Lauren%20Makler%2C%20and%20Arielle%20Spiegel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63519876390dfe00196d4a29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECofertility%20cofounders%20Tecco%2C%20Lauren%20Makler%2C%20and%20Arielle%20Spiegel.%3Cp%3ECofertility%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETecco%20entered%20healthcare%20not%20solely%20to%20invest%20in%20startups%2C%20or%20to%20build%20her%20own%2C%20but%20to%20help%20other%20aspiring%20healthcare%20entrepreneurs%20with%20fresh%20perspectives%20and%20technologies%20in%20clearing%20the%20industry's%20many%20hurdles.%20Now%2041%20years%20old%2C%20she%20wants%20to%20get%20back%20to%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20she's%20been%20focused%20on%20writing%20a%20book%20with%20that%20very%20thesis%2C%20aiming%20to%20pass%20along%20her%20knowledge%20to%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20healthcare%20builders.%20She%20sees%20it%20as%20the%20natural%20next%20step%20up%20from%20her%20blog%2C%20where%20she's%20covered%20topics%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.halletecco.com%2Fblog%2Fshould-i-get-an-mba-or-mph-if-i-want-to-work-in-digital-health%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20value%20of%20an%20MBA%20versus%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20public%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%20(both%20degrees%20that%20Tecco%20holds)%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.halletecco.com%2Fblog%2Fwhy-your-st