rocess%20is%20kicking%20off.%20Here's%20an%20inside%20look%20at%20its%20unpopular%20method.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22citi%20bank%20sad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66436bf8b4abc992e8c93ddd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECiti%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECiti%20rates%20its%20200%2C000%20employees%20on%20a%20forced%20curve%20that%20assesses%20peers%20from%20best%20to%20worst.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThese%20rankings%20influence%20who%20gets%20promoted%20and%20who%20loses%20their%20bonus%20%E2%80%94%20or%20worse.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EManaging%20directors%20told%20BI%20how%20the%20process%20works%20and%20why%20it%20can%20pit%20employees%20against%20each%20other.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECitigroup%20welcomed%20344%20new%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fciti-managing-director-promotions-names-jane-fraser-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emanaging%20directors%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20marking%20its%20biggest%20class%20in%20years.%20Behind%20the%20scenes%2C%20the%20promotion%20process%20can%20be%20political%20and%20fraught%2C%20pitting%20employees%20against%20each%20other%2C%20four%20current%20and%20former%20managing%20directors%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECiti%20evaluates%20employees%20on%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstack-ranking-employees-is-a-bad-idea-2013-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eforced%20curve%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20requiring%20managers%20to%20rank%20them%20from%20best%20to%20worst%20using%20a%20four-level%20scale%20with%20a%20certain%20percentage%20in%20each%20bucket.%20This%20system%20means%20there's%20a%20finite%20number%20of%20top%20ratings%2C%20so%20employees%20could%20exceed%20all%20the%20requirements%20of%20their%20role%20and%20still%20receive%20a%20middling%20grade%2C%20said%20the%20employees%2C%20who%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20a%20company%20filled%20with%20hardworking%2C%20achievement-oriented%20colleagues%20and%20we%20embrace%20meritocracy%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Citi%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20written%20statement.%20%26quot%3BOur%20process%20aims%20to%20ensure%20that%20colleagues%20across%20Citi%20are%20held%20to%20consistent%20standards%20and%20are%20assessed%20by%20those%20who%20have%20the%20most%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20their%20contributions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20the%20percentage%20ranges%20for%20each%20bracket%20have%20shifted%20slightly.%20A%20managing%20director%20said%20this%20year%20each%20business%20line%20could%20assign%20top%20ratings%20of%201%20(%26quot%3Bexemplary%26quot%3B)%20and%202%20(%26quot%3Bexceeds%20expectations%26quot%3B)%20to%205%25%20to%2010%25%20and%2015%25%20to%2030%25%20of%20staff%2C%20respectively.%20The%20lion's%20share%20of%20employees%20%E2%80%94%2050%25%20to%2065%25%20%E2%80%94%20are%20labeled%20as%20%26quot%3Bvalued%20contributors.%26quot%3B%20The%20remaining%203%25%20to%207%25%20who%20receive%20a%204%20rating%20(%26quot%3Bneeds%20improvement%26quot%3B)%20may%20face%20consequences%20such%20as%20being%20put%20on%20a%20performance%20improvement%20plan%20or%20losing%20bonus%20eligibility.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt%20creates%20an%20air%20of%20distrust%20inside%20of%20cultures%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20anxiety%20for%20employees%20that%20are%20high%20performers%20but%20may%20not%20be%20recognized%20for%20the%20work%20they%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Frehse%2C%20a%20senior%20managing%20director%20at%20the%20management%20consultancy%20Ankura%2C%20said%20about%20the%20ranking%20practice.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jane%20Fraser%20speaking%20at%20the%20Milken%20Insitute%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64514e388b6329001b556b51%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECiti%20CEO%20Jane%20Fraser.%3Cp%3EPatrick%20T.%20Fallon%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20same%20morning%20the%20new%20class%20of%20managing%20directors%20was%20announced%2C%20Citi%20held%20a%20virtual%20town%20hall%20for%20employees.%20During%20the%20Q%26amp%3BA%20session%2C%20human%20resources%20addressed%20an%20employee's%20written%20question%20that%20noted%20the%20forced%20distribution%20system%20could%20be%20unfair%20to%20small%2C%20high-performing%20teams.%20Sara%20Wechter%2C%20Citi's%20head%20of%20human%20resources%2C%20replied%20that%20there%20was%20no%20forced%20bell%20curve.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20senior%20Citi%20executive%20familiar%20with%20the%20process%20told%20BI%20that%20Citi's%20curve%20is%20not%20forced%20as%20it%20uses%20brackets%20rather%20than%20fixed%20percentages.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20guidelines%20associated%20with%20ratings%2C%20which%20is%20different%20from%20a%20forced%20curve%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20reasoning%20is%20of%20little%20comfort%20to%20employees%20BI%20spoke%20to%20who%20assign%20those%20ratings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20playing%20with%20words%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20managing%20director%20in%20the%20wealth%20division.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20mandated%20to%20strictly%20follow%20the%20prescribed%20curve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20season's%20annual%20reviews%2C%20which%20began%20last%20week%2C%20play%20a%20key%20role%20in%20bonus%20allocations%20and%20promotions%2C%20including%20to%20managing%20director.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20come%20at%20a%20tense%20time%20for%20Citi's%20workforce.%20As%20part%20of%20CEO%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fciti-jane-fraser-regulators-occ-frb-consent-orders-asset-cap-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EJane%20Fraser's%20mission%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20turn%20around%20the%20bank%2C%20Citi%20has%20laid%20off%207%2C000%20employees%20and%20divested%20from%20several%20businesses.%20The%20overhaul%20isn't%20over%2C%20with%20the%20bank%20planning%20to%20cut%2020%2C000%20jobs%20from%20its%20workforce%20of%20more%20than%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcitigroup-lay-off-workers-jobs-restructuring-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E200%2C000%20employees%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%202026.%20Amid%20these%20changes%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20said%20there's%20more%20anxiety%20about%20the%20review%20process%20and%20uncertainty%20about%20bonuses.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22082acff8-96ce-45bd-9b89-dc0461c5a8ed%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHere's%20how%20Citi's%20forced%20curve%20works%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGrading%20on%20a%20forced%20curve%20is%20not%20unique%20to%20Citi.%20The%20practice%2C%20otherwise%20known%20as%20stack%20ranking%2C%20was%20popularized%20in%20the%201980s%20when%20General%20Electric's%20former%20CEO%20Jack%20Welch%20used%20it%20to%20cut%20bottom%20performers.%20However%2C%20this%20%26quot%3Brank%20and%20yank%26quot%3B%20tactic%20has%20fallen%20out%20of%20fashion%20with%20many%20major%20companies%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-new-employee-review-system-stack-ranking-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20Amazon.%20Most%20banks%20engage%20in%20some%20form%20of%20stack%20ranking%20but%20the%20details%20differ%2C%20such%20as%20how%20strictly%20they%20adhere%20to%20a%20curve%20or%20the%20grading%20criteria%20they%20use.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMorgan%20Stanley%20uses%20a%20five-point%20scale.%20Goldman%20Sachs%20has%20changed%20its%20system%20several%20times%20and%2C%20beginning%20in%202020%2C%20it's%20used%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-goldman-sachs-annual-performance-reviews-work-wall-street-layoffs-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethree-level%20system%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BGood%20companies%20try%20to%20distinguish%20between%20the%20higher%20and%20lower%20performers%20and%20do%20that%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20people%20get%20raises%2C%20what%20their%20total%20compensation%20would%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Anthony%20Nyberg%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20the%20Darla%20Moore%20School%20of%20Business%20at%20the%20University%20of%20South%20Carolina.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECiti%20employees%20receive%20two%20main%20ratings%20with%20each%20one%20graded%20on%20a%20curve%2C%20two%20ex-managing%20directors%20said.%20The%20two%20criteria%20are%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhat%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20measures%20an%20employee's%20results%2C%20such%20as%20revenue%20metrics%2C%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bhow%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20evaluates%20their%20approach%20and%20leadership%20abilities.%20This%20means%20employees%20get%20a%20combination%20score%20such%20as%201-2.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20it%20is%20not%20a%20hard%20and%20fast%20rule%2C%20Citi%20employees%20are%20usually%20expected%20to%20earn%20top%20ratings%20for%20two%20to%20three%20consecutive%20years%20to%20receive%20a%20promotion%2C%20so%20the%20review%20process%20puts%20aspiring%20directors%20and%20managing%20directors%20under%20enormous%20pressure%2C%20three%20of%20the%20managing%20directors%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDirect%20managers%20submit%20their%20ratings%20for%20review%20before%20having%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bcalibration%26quot%3B%20meeting%20with%20their%20fellow%20managers%2C%20the%20top%20manager%20of%20their%20business%20unit%2C%20and%20an%20HR%20representative%2C%20the%20two%20former%20executives%20said.%20At%20these%20meetings%2C%20direct%20managers%20review%20an%20employee's%20scores%20and%20make%20a%20case%20for%20why%20the%20employee%20deserves%20a%20coveted%201%20or%202.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20these%20calibration%20meetings%2C%20the%20top%20manager%20makes%20the%20final%20call%20on%20rankings.%20The%20outcome%20often%20disappoints%20managers%20and%20their%20reports%2C%20who%20may%20have%20never%20worked%20directly%20with%20the%20decision-maker%2C%20the%20managing%20directors%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20senior%20executive%20said%20that%20small%20teams%20of%20three%20or%20four%20employees%20can%20secure%20exemptions%20to%20the%20curve.%20As%20for%20large%20teams%20with%20high%20performers%2C%20he%20said%20there%20might%20be%20exceptions%20on%20a%20year-to-year%20basis%20but%20he%20wasn't%20aware%20of%20any%20ever%20happening.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22984fe344-3506-464d-a576-f8ba8ffc58ff%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMDs%20said%20the%20process%20pits%20employees%20against%20each%20other%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20evaluation%20process%20was%20described%20as%20contentious%20and%20stressful%20by%20the%20current%20and%20former%20managing%20directors%2C%20all%20of%20whom%20were%20responsible%20for%20rating%20employees.%20The%20calibration%20meetings%20were%20especially%20heated%2C%20with%20managers%20butting%20heads%20over%20which%20employees%20received%20the%20limited%20high%20ratings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20the%20number%20of%20top%20rankings%20is%20fixed%2C%20managers%20were%20typically%20unwilling%20to%20budge%20on%20the%201s%20and%202s%20they%20were%20allotted%2C%20even%20if%20another%20manager%20argued%20they%20had%20more%20high%20performers.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20was%20like%2C%20'You%20can%20take%20mine%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20of%20the%20ex-managing%20directors%2C%20who%20left%20Citi%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BWe%20fought.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20managers%20took%20issue%20with%20other%20aspects%20of%20the%20grading%20process.%20By%20implementing%20a%20curve%20on%20the%20team%20level%2C%20employees%20were%20sometimes%20compared%20to%20others%20with%20vastly%20disparate%20roles%20or%20responsibilities.%20Two%20of%20the%20ex-managing%20directors%20described%20some%20of%20the%20grading%20criteria%20as%20nebulous.%20For%20instance%2C%20they%20said%2C%20for%20employees%20with%20non-revenue-generating%20roles%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhat%26quot%3B%20score%20is%20effectively%20up%20to%20the%20manager's%20discretion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrehse%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20biggest%20flaw%20with%20stacked%20ranking%20is%20that%20performance%20reviews%20are%20inherently%20subjective.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BStack%20ranking%20is%20inaccurate%20from%20the%20start%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20either%20only%20looking%20at%20the%20quantitative%20side%2C%20forgetting%20about%20the%20other%20side%2C%20or%20you're%20looking%20at%20both.%20And%20we%20know%20that%20the%20qualitative%20side%20is%20flawed%20and%20subjective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrehse%20said%20that%20leaves%20room%20for%20employees%20to%20believe%20favoritism%20is%20at%20work.%20Three%20of%20the%20managing%20directors%20told%20BI%20that%20they%20believed%20internal%20politics%20played%20a%20role%20in%20how%20employees%20were%20ranked%20and%20which%20managers%20received%20top%20ratings%20for%20their%20direct%20reports.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20use%20such%20a%20system%2C%20it%20tells%20you%20you%20can't%20trust%20different%20managers%20to%20be%20good%20managers%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20of%20the%20former%20managing%20directors.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20senior%20executive%20said%20that%20the%20many%20calibration%20meetings%20he%20attended%20were%20productive.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20a%20way%20to%20get%20together%2C%20get%20out%20of%20the%20silos%2C%20and%20make%20sure%20that%20there's%20fairness%20and%20perspective%20that%20goes%20beyond%20your%20own%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20he%20maintained%20that%20he%20had%20not%20seen%20hostile%20calibration%20meetings%2C%20he%20said%20that%20some%20conversations%20could%20get%20heated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20very%20human%20thing%20when%20you%20have%20finite%20anything%2C%20and%20obviously%20we%20have%20finite%20compensation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20people%20are%20aware%20of%20that%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20a%20flaw%20in%20the%20design.%20I%20think%20that's%20just%20part%20of%20being%20human.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20its%20best%2C%20stacked%20ranking%20should%20reduce%20anxiety%20among%20employees%2C%20Nyberg%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20get%20very%20upset%20when%20things%20appear%20to%20be%20arbitrary%2C%20and%20the%20ranking%20system%20should%20actually%20reduce%20some%20of%20that%20as%20long%20as%20people%20can%20believe%20that%20you're%20doing%20those%20rankings%20in%20some%20sort%20of%20objective%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20it's%20hard%20for%20employees%20to%20trust%20the%20system%20if%20they%20lose%20trust%20in%20their%20employers%2C%20which%20often%20happens%20after%20layoffs%2C%20Nyberg%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20that%20contract%20between%20the%20organization%20and%20the%20employees%20starts%20to%20feel%20really%20violated%20that%20way%2C%20and%20then%20that%20permeates%20everything%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthen%20you%20wouldn't%20believe%20anything%20they%20say.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcitibank-annual-employee-review-process-rankings-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734513181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66436bf8b4abc992e8c93ddd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcitibank-annual-employee-review-process-rankings-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Citi%20ranks%20employees%20with%20a%20widely%20used%20yet%20oft-criticized%20method.%20Managers%20told%20BI%20how%20it%20works.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hcuccinello%40businessinsider.com%20(Hayley%20Cuccinello)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcitibank-annual-employee-review-process-rankings-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Xi%20Jinping%20visits%20Macau%20to%20mark%2025%20years%20of%20Chinese%20rule%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734513131000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-116431861%2Cimgsize-1487915.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fxi-jinping-visits-macau-to-mark-25-years-of-chinese-rule%2Farticleshow%2F116431676.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F116431676.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EChinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20arrived%20in%20Macau%20to%20commemorate%2025%20years%20of%20Chinese%20rule%20and%20attend%20the%20new%20chief%20executive's%20inauguration.%20Xi's%20visit%20emphasizes%20the%20need%20for%20Macau%20to%20