urity%20facing%20workers%20without%20retirement%20plans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThose%20workers%20would%20likely%20have%20difficulty%20living%20solely%20off%20Social%20Security.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMany%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAmericans%20don't%20feel%20ready%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-pensions-student-loan-debt-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20their%20jobs%20aren't%20stepping%20in%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-baby-boomers-savings-cant-afford-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efill%20in%20the%20economic%20gaps%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aarp.org%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Faarp%2Fppi%2Ftopics%2Fwork-finances-retirement%2Ffinancial-security-retirement%2F2024-payroll-deduction-retirement-fact-sheets%2Fpayroll-deduction-retirement-programs-build-economic-security.doi.10.26419-2fppi.00164.001.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20AARP%20Public%20Policy%20Institute%20finds%20that%2C%20in%202022%2C%2056%20million%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%20private-sector%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%20worked%20for%20employers%20who%20didn't%20offer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-401k-pension-real-estate-investments-baby-boomers-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epension%20or%20retirement%20savings%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20with%20less%20education%20and%20lower%20earnings%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20access%20to%20plans.%20Specifically%2C%20AARP%20said%20that%20about%2075%25%20of%20private-sector%20workers%20with%20less%20than%20a%20high%20school%20degree%2C%2050%25%20of%20workers%20with%20some%20college%2C%20and%2031%25%20of%20workers%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20do%20not%20have%20a%20retirement%20plan.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20about%2079%25%20of%20workers%20earning%20%2453%2C000%20or%20less%20annually%20and%2021%25%20of%20workers%20earning%20over%20%2453%2C000%20do%20not%20have%20retirement%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20John%2C%20one%20of%20the%20AARP%20report's%20authors%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20even%20while%20those%20workers%20would%20get%20Social%20Security%20benefits%2C%20they%20likely%20wouldn't%20be%20enough%20to%20supplement%20other%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20is%20that%20if%20you%20are%20a%20career%20lower-income%20individual%2C%20yes%2C%20Social%20Security%20is%20going%20to%20replace%20a%20higher%20proportion%20of%20your%20earnings%2C%20but%20you%20still%20have%20the%20emergencies%20that%20are%20going%20to%20come%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20includes%20things%20like%20car%20repair%2C%20cost%20of%20medication%2C%20house%20repair%20%E2%80%94%20hot%20water%20heaters%20don't%20really%20care%20who%20you%20are%20at%20the%20time%20they%20decide%20to%20fail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FpemUB%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Workers%20who%20don't%20have%20access%20to%20a%20retirement%20plan%20by%20earnings%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22329%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AARP%20report%20said%20that%2C%20with%20the%20average%20Social%20Security%20benefit%20totaling%20around%20%241%2C767%20a%20month%20in%202022%2C%20most%20retirees%20will%20need%20additional%20income%20sources%20to%20stay%20financially%20afloat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20substantial%20number%20of%20people%20who%20don't%20have%20sufficient%20retirement%20savings%20to%20supplement%20their%20Social%20Security.%20Social%20Security%20is%20it%20for%20a%20substantial%20number%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20means%2C%20essentially%2C%20that%20they%20may%20not%20have%20the%20kind%20of%20retirement%20that%20they%20dreamed%20of.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20uses%20data%20from%20the%20Census%20Bureau's%20Current%20Population%20Survey%20on%20employer%20coverage%2C%20which%20provides%20data%20on%20Americans'%20work%2C%20earnings%2C%20and%20education%2C%20and%20adjusts%20it%20by%20factoring%20in%20additional%20data%20from%20the%20Survey%20of%20Consumer%20Finances%20and%20IRS%20to%20bring%20the%20findings%20in%20line%20with%20the%20overall%20population%2C%20allowing%20the%20researchers%20to%20break%20out%20specific%20demographic%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20security%20remains%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeak-boomer-scared-to-retire-working-depleted-savings-social-security-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etop%20concern%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20many%20older%20adults.%20A%20recent%20report%20from%20the%20Alliance%20for%20Lifetime%20Income's%20Retirement%20Income%20Institute%20found%20that%20in%202024%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-retirement-of-peak-boomers-could-affect-economy-social-security-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%2030%20million%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20born%20between%201959%20and%201964%20%E2%80%94%20the%20tail%20end%20of%20the%20baby%20boomer%20generation%20%E2%80%94%20will%20start%20turning%2065%2C%20meaning%20many%20of%20them%20will%20increasingly%20start%20to%20rely%20on%20retirement%20savings.%20Without%20a%20retirement%20plan%2C%20some%20previously%20told%20BI%20they%20would%20likely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeak-boomer-scared-to-retire-working-depleted-savings-social-security-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20to%20continue%20working%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20supplement%20their%20Social%20Security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%20have%20taken%20steps%20to%20aid%20workers%20who%20do%20not%20have%20access%20to%20retirement%20plans%20through%20their%20employers.%20California%20created%20a%20program%20in%202019%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.calsavers.com%2Fhome%2Fabout.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalSavers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20requires%20employers%20in%20the%20state%20who%20do%20not%20sponsor%20a%20retirement%20plan%20to%20provide%20individual%20retirement%20accounts%20that%20employees%20are%20automatically%20enrolled%20into%20unless%20they%20opt%20out.%20John%20said%20that%20some%20variation%20on%20that%20type%20of%20plan%20could%20work%20at%20the%20federal%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20basic%20model%20or%20the%20basic%20way%20the%20state%20programs%20are%20structured%20can%20be%20a%20guide%20to%20help%20create%20a%20national%20solution%20to%20the%20retirement%20coverage%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare%20Board%20of%20Trustees%20report%20found%20that%20Social%20Security%20will%20only%20be%20able%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-social-security-benefits-run-out-retirement-crisis-boomers-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epay%20out%20full%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20next%2011%20years%20if%20Congress%20does%20not%20intervene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20said%20that%20the%20lack%20of%20coverage%20goes%20beyond%20just%20weighing%20down%20individuals%20%E2%80%94%20it%20could%20also%20have%20a%20drag%20on%20the%20wider%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20have%20a%20substantial%20number%20of%20people%20who%20don't%20have%20sufficient%20resources%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20put%20pressure%20on%20governments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Those%20retirees%20will%20likely%20be%20more%20dependent%20on%20government%20programs%20like%20housing%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20senior%20citizen%20centers.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20an%20expense%20to%20the%20economy%20and%20there%20is%20an%20expense%20to%20frankly%20the%20future%20by%20not%20dealing%20with%20this%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20not%20receive%20retirement%20benefits%20through%20work%20and%20are%20worried%20about%20your%20future%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejkaplan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployer-sponsored-retirement-plans-social-security-savings-boomers-aarp-report-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734512402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675c64e757df667cc5a62848%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployer-sponsored-retirement-plans-social-security-savings-boomers-aarp-report-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nearly%20half%20of%20Americans%20don't%20get%20retirement%20plans%20at%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CAyelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployer-sponsored-retirement-plans-social-security-savings-boomers-aarp-report-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20chip%20company%20you%20probably%20never%20heard%20of%20is%20suddenly%20worth%20%241%20trillion.%20Here's%20why%2C%20and%20what%20it%20means%20for%20Nvidia.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224852%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Broadcom%20CEO%20Hock%20Tan%20speaking%20at%20a%20conference%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%